		<p class="bmenu">New and Noteworthy</p>
		<p><a class="menu" href="/updates/">Recently Updated Pages</a></p>

		<div id="newsitem">
		<p><a class="news" href="http://alac.icann.org/announcements/announcement-16dec03.htm">ICANN Certifies "At-Large Structures" in Europe, Asia-Pacific and Latin America: Involvement of Global Individual User Community Increasing in ICANN</a><br>
		<i>16 December 2003</i> -  In an important step towards fulfilling the Internet Corporation for Assigned Names and Numbers' (ICANN's) objective to have informed, structured participation of the individual Internet user community ("At-Large"), six organizations in three geographic regions have received "At-Large Structure" certification.<br>
		<a class="news" href="http://alac.icann.org/announcements/announcement-espanol-16dec03.htm">En espa&ntilde;ol</a>
		</p>
		</div>
		<div id="newsitem">
		<p><a class="news" href="/announcements/announcement-15dec03.htm">ICANN Releases Request for Proposal for Sponsored Top Level Domain Names</a><br>
		<i>15 December 2003</i> - ICANN is inviting applications from all parties wishing apply for new sTLDs. Interested parties can view the Request for Proposal (RFP) on ICANN's website.</p>
		</div>
		<div id="newsitem">
		<p><a class="news" href="/correspondence/twomey-to-wsis-11dec03.htm">Speech by Dr Paul Twomey</a><br>
		<i>11 December 2003</i> - Speech given by Dr. Paul Twomey, President and CEO of ICANN, at the plenary
session of the World Summit for the Information Society (WSIS).</p>
		</div>
		<div id="newsitem">
		<p><a class="news" href="/gnso/issue-reports/registry-svcs-report-19nov03.htm">Staff Manager's Issue Report on the Need for a Predictable Procedure for Changes in the Operation of TLD Registries</a><br>
		<i>19 November 2003</i> -  The ICANN community, and the Internet community at large have expressed interest in the process for consideration of changes in the operation of a TLD registry. The opinions expressed indicate that there be a predictable process prior to implementation of such changes that allows for an assessment of the potential effect on Internet operations, with due consideration given to all relevant factors - including the legitimate interests of the TLD operator. <font class="red">Updated 2 December 2003</font></p>
		</div>
		
		<div id="newsitem">
		<p><a class="news" href="/announcements/advisory-13nov03.htm">Advisory: U.S. Federal Court Denies Plaintiffs' Request for Preliminary Injunction in Dotster v. ICANN Lawsuit</a><br>
		<i>13 November 2003</i> - In a strongly worded ruling, a U.S. Federal Court Judge has ruled in ICANN's favor and denied plaintiffs' motion for preliminary injunction.</p>
		</div>
		<div id="newsitem">
        <p><a class="news" href="/announcements/announcement-10nov03.htm">ICANN Announces Appointment of General Manager, IANA</a><br>
		<i>10 November 2003</i> -  ICANN is pleased to announce that Mr. Doug Barton will be joining the company as General Manager, IANA. Given his technical training and experience working with the Domain Name System (DNS), Mr. Barton is particularly well suited for the position.</p>
		</div>
		<div id="newsitem">
		<p><a class="news" href="/announcements/announcement-07nov03.htm">ICANN Mourns Loss of Former Board Member</a><br>
		<i>7 November 2003</i> - The ICANN Board mourns the loss of its former member and colleague, Hans Kraaijenbrink, who passed away Nov 5, 2003. Hans served as an ICANN director from the creation of ICANN in 1998 until June 2003. He played a key role in the evolution and reform of ICANN during the past 18 months, seeking always to balance the interests of many constituencies.<br>
		<a class="news" href="/announcements/announcement-dutch-07nov03.htm">ICANN betreurt overlijden van voormalig bestuurslid</a></p>
		</div>
            <div id="newsitem">
                <p><a class="news" href="/transfers/">Information About New Transfer Policy Procedure</a><br>
				<i>5 November 2003</i> - The new transfer policy is intended to provide a procedure for the smooth transition of a domain name from one registrar to another when such a change is requested by the domain name holder. The Transfer Task Force Group has developed 29 policy recommendations for guiding such transfers. The Transfer Assistance Group (TAG) along with ICANN Staff, is currently in the process of implementing the new transfer procedures, based on the 29 policy recommendations, approved by the ICANN Board.</p>
           </div>

